The determination of a fit-for-purpose sampling frequency can contain the following steps: 
	61 identify the activities at the farm in which water is applied; 
	62 identify the sources of water available for the farm; 
	63 evaluate the use of water in relation to the potential contamination to edible parts of the fresh produce; 
	64 check the quality of the water before its use (before the start of the growth season); and 
	65 monitor the quality of water regularly during the growing period.i 
A risk-based approach can be used for determining testing frequency.
